{"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnoverlay\/overlaybounds"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["occ"],"platforms":["iOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"@property"},{"kind":"text","text":" ("},{"kind":"keyword","text":"nonatomic"},{"kind":"text","text":", "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"readonly"},{"kind":"text","text":") "},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNCoordinateBounds","preciseIdentifier":"c:@S@MLNCoordinateBounds","text":"MLNCoordinateBounds"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"overlayBounds"},{"kind":"text","text":";"}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","anchor":"discussion","text":"Discussion","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This property contains the smallest rectangle that completely encompasses the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"overlay. Implementers of this protocol must set this area when implementing","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"their overlay class, and after setting it, you must not change it.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If this overlay spans the antimeridian, its bounds may extend west of −180 degrees"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"longitude or east of 180 degrees longitude. For example, an overlay covering the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Pacific Ocean from Tokyo to San Francisco might have a bounds extending"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"from (35.68476, −220.24257) to (37.78428, −122.41310)."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"abstract":[{"text":"The cooordinate rectangle that encompasses the overlay. (required) (read-only)","type":"text"}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay\/overlayBounds","interfaceLanguage":"occ"},"metadata":{"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"overlayBounds","kind":"identifier"}],"modules":[{"name":"MapLibre"}],"symbolKind":"property","externalID":"c:objc(pl)MLNOverlay(py)overlayBounds","roleHeading":"Instance Property","role":"symbol","title":"overlayBounds","fragments":[{"text":"overlayBounds","kind":"identifier"}]},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"sections":[],"kind":"symbol","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay"]]},"references":{"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNOverlay/overlayBounds":{"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The cooordinate rectangle that encompasses the overlay. (required) (read-only)"}],"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnoverlay\/overlaybounds","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay\/overlayBounds","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"overlayBounds"}],"title":"overlayBounds","role":"symbol"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNCoordinateBounds":{"type":"topic","title":"MLNCoordinateBounds","abstract":[{"text":"A rectangular area as measured on a two-dimensional map projection.","type":"text"}],"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlncoordinatebounds","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNCoordinateBounds"}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNCoordinateBounds"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Powerful, free and open-source mapping toolkit with full control over data sources and styling."}],"role":"collection","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","title":"MapLibre"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNOverlay":{"title":"MLNOverlay","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNOverlay"}],"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol defines a specific type of annotation that represents"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"both a point and an area on a map. Overlay objects are essentially data objects"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that contain the geographic data needed to represent the map area. Overlays can"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"take the form of a polyline or polygon."}],"role":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnoverlay"}}}